Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. In medium bowl, stir together wafer crumbs, cocoa and sugar; cut in butter until crumble. Press mixture evenly on bottom and 1/2-inch up sides of ungreased 13x9-inch baking pan. Pour EAGLE BRAND(R) evenly over crumb mixture; sprinkle evenly on top with peanut butter chips, dried cranberries and nuts; press down firmly. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool completely in pan on wire rack. Cover with foil. Let stand several hours. Cut into bars. Store covered at room temperature.